Directed 5-cycle count on n=5 tournaments:
  0 directed 5-cycles: 480 tournaments (46.9%)
  1 directed 5-cycles: 360 tournaments (35.2%)
  2 directed 5-cycles: 144 tournaments (14.1%)
  3 directed 5-cycles: 40 tournaments (3.9%)

Note: each cyclic rotation gives the same cycle, and we fixed
start vertex=0, so these are DISTINCT directed cycles.

Total with ≥2: 184

============================================================
Impact on OCF:
============================================================
If a 5-element set has c directed 5-cycles:
  Vertex-set approach: contributes 1 to α₁ (wrong)
  Directed-cycle approach: contributes c to α₁ (correct)
  These c cycles are all in a clique, so they contribute
  I(K_c, 2) - 1 = 2c to H (not 2·1 = 2)

  c=1: correct contribution = 2·1 = 2
         vs-approach contribution = 2·1 = 2  
  c=2: correct contribution = 2·2 = 4
         vs-approach contribution = 2·1 = 2  ← ERROR!
  c=3: correct contribution = 2·3 = 6
         vs-approach contribution = 2·1 = 2  ← ERROR!
